>[Question]
>I am painting my house.  I need to know how to figure how much paint I
>will need.  The house is 40.5 ft wide and 8ft tall on the front and
>back.  The sides are 24.4 ft times 8 ft tall. The garage is 16 ft
>front and back.  What would the square ft be?
>
>
>
>
>
>[Difficulty]
>Square foot would be width times height, but in this case that doesn't
>seem to be enough, as the paint gallon says it covers 400 sq ft per
>gallon.
>
>[Thoughts]
>40.4 * 8 ft= 323.2 * 2= 646.4
>24.4 * 8 ft = 195.2 * 2 = 390.4
>16 ft * 8 ft =128 * 2 = 256
>
>256 + 646.4 + 390.4 = 1292.8
>There is no way 3 gallons of paint on this whole house would be
>enough?  Is there?
>
>

